---
import PageLayout from '@theme/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy policy for mbpstobytes.com—what we collect, what we don’t, and how this Mbps to Bytes converter handles data.">
  <section class="space-y-5 mt-4 text-slate-700">
    <p>This Privacy Policy explains how mbpstobytes.com (“we”, “us”, “our”) handles information when you use our website and conversion tools.</p>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">1) Summary (plain English)</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 pl-6 list-disc">
      <li><strong>No account required:</strong> you can use the converter without signing up.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Your inputs stay on your device:</strong> the numbers you type into the calculator are processed in your browser to compute results (we do not intentionally “collect” your entered values unless you send them to us).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>We may collect basic site analytics:</strong> limited, aggregated metrics to understand performance and improve UX.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">2) What we collect</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 pl-6 list-disc">
      <li>
        <strong>Usage data (optional/limited):</strong> aggregated information such as page views, approximate region, device type, and referral source. This helps us measure performance and improve the calculator.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Server logs:</strong> standard web server logs (e.g., IP address, user-agent, timestamps, requested pages). These are used for security, troubleshooting, and reliability.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Messages you send:</strong> if you contact us via the <a href="/contact-us/" class="text-sky-800 hover:underline">contact page</a>, we receive the information you submit (such as name, email, and message content).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Preference data (on-device):</strong> the site may store simple preferences (like your decimals setting) in your browser (e.g., localStorage) to improve usability. This stays on your device unless your browser shares it.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">3) What we do not collect by default</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 pl-6 list-disc">
      <li>We do not require usernames or passwords to use the tool.</li>
      <li>We do not collect payment details because the calculator is free to use.</li>
      <li>We do not intentionally collect the specific conversion values you type into the calculator (unless you include them in a message you send us).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">4) How we use information</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 pl-6 list-disc">
      <li>Provide, maintain, and improve the converter and site performance</li>
      <li>Secure the Service, prevent abuse, and troubleshoot issues</li>
      <li>Respond to messages and support requests</li>
      <li>Understand which pages/features are most useful (aggregated analytics)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">5) Cookies & analytics</h2>
    <p>We may use cookies or similar technologies for essential site functionality and (optionally) privacy-respecting analytics. If non-essential cookies are used where legally required, we will provide notice and choices.</p>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">6) Sharing</h2>
    <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share limited data with trusted service providers who help run the site (e.g., hosting, security, analytics). Providers are expected to process data only for providing their services and to protect it appropriately. We may also disclose information if required by law or to protect rights, safety, or the integrity of the Service.</p>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">7) Retention</h2>
    <p>We keep server logs and analytics for a limited period consistent with security and operational needs. Contact messages are retained as long as needed to respond and maintain reasonable records.</p>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">8) Your choices & rights</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 pl-6 list-disc">
      <li>You can use the calculator without providing personal information.</li>
      <li>You can disable cookies via your browser settings (some features may work less smoothly).</li>
      <li>
        Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or restrict processing of your personal data. To make a request, contact us via the <a href="/contact-us/" class="text-sky-800 hover:underline">contact page</a>.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">9) Data security</h2>
    <p>We take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect information. However, no internet service is 100% secure. Please use the Service at your own discretion.</p>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">10) Children</h2>
    <p>This site is not directed to children under 13 (or the age required by local law). If you believe a child provided personal information, please contact us so we can delete it.</p>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">11) Changes</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If changes are material, we’ll take reasonable steps to notify you (e.g., posting a notice on the site).</p>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">12) Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about privacy? Reach out via the <a href="/contact-us/" class="text-sky-800 hover:underline">contact page</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Last updated: December 6, 2025</p>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
